                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12971453" author="zznate" created="Tue, 14 Dec 2010 22:42:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes exception type to UnavailalbeException&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971700" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 15:10:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971705" author="hudson" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 15:24:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.7 #83 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/83/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/83/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    change exceptionfor readrequests duringbootstrap from InvalidRequest to Unavailable&lt;br/&gt;
patch by Nate McCall; reviewed by jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1862&quot; title=&quot;StorageProxy throws an InvalidRequestException in readProtocol during bootstrap&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1862&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1862&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971729" author="zznate" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 16:32:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Backport to 0.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971736" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 16:50:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m a little leery of breaking 0.6 compatibility for something fairly minor.  Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971751" author="zznate" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 17:38:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is extremely minor (the exception declaration of the method did not change) and brings us in line with the API as specified in cassandra.thrift: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IRE:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Invalid request could mean keyspace or column family does not exist, required parameters are missing, or a parameter is malformed...&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;vs. UE:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Not all the replicas required could be created and/or read.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971754" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 17:43:14 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;the exception declaration of the method did not change&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i&apos;ll buy that.  committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12971764" author="hudson" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 18:14:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.6 #24 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.6/24/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.6/24/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    backport &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1862&quot; title=&quot;StorageProxy throws an InvalidRequestException in readProtocol during bootstrap&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1862&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1862&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from 0.7&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13022179" author="doubleday" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2011 15:40:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t know wether commenting a closed jira makes sense but I think that this made matters worse because now bootstrapping is not distinguishable anymore.&lt;br/&gt;
I thought that UnavailableException would signal that a read cannot be served due to CL. And a bootstrapping coordinator does not imply this right? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
